The paper deals with the learning complexity of simulated annealing, which is a topic that falls under the broad area of machine learning. Specifically, the paper discusses the sample and simulation complexity of designing optimal cooling schedules for simulated annealing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
